Sorry, but Korean skincare won’t magically give you glass skin if you’re Indian! 💁‍♀️🌍

Our skin thrives in a whole different vibe—more melanin, tropical climate, and unique concerns like tanning & pigmentation.

The secret? Adapt, don’t copy. 🧴✨
Focus on sunscreen, hydration, and actives that suit YOUR skin’s needs.

Healthy, glowing skin > chasing unrealistic beauty standards! #SkinRealTalk

💬 Comment below—what’s the one skincare step you never skip? 👀✨

You don’t need a fancy 10-step routine—just the right steps! Here’s a basic skincare routine that works for EVERYONE:

🌞 Morning:
🧼 Cleanser – Wash off sweat & oil
💦 Moisturizer – Keep skin hydrated
🛡️ Sunscreen – Non-negotiable! SPF every single day

🌙 Night:
🧴 Cleanser – Remove dirt, oil & sunscreen
🌙 Moisturizer – Lock in hydration overnight

That’s it—simple, effective, and actually sustainable! Who else loves a no-BS routine? 🙋‍♀️

Let’s break down the IT serums you need in your routine and how to use them right! 👇

🌞 Vitamin C – Glow booster & antioxidant shield!
✔️ Brightens skin & evens tone
✔️ Fights free radicals & sun damage
❌ Avoid mixing with AHAs/BHAs & retinol
⏰ Best used in AM with SPF for max protection!

🌟 Niacinamide – The all-rounder MVP!
✔️ Controls oil, minimizes pores, strengthens barrier
✔️ Fades dark spots & reduces redness
❌ Don’t mix with high % Vitamin C (can cause irritation)
⏰ AM or PM—super versatile!

🌙 Retinol – Anti-aging powerhouse!
✔️ Speeds up cell turnover, smooths wrinkles, clears acne
✔️ Stimulates collagen for firmer skin
❌ Avoid if pregnant & never mix with AHAs/BHAs/Vit C
⏰ PM only—start slow (2-3x a week) & always wear SPF next day!

💦 Hyaluronic Acid – The ultimate hydration hero!
✔️ Binds moisture, plumps skin, keeps it juicy
✔️ Works for ALL skin types
❌ Always apply on damp skin & seal with a moisturizer
⏰ AM & PM—your skin will drink it up!

Which serum is your ride-or-die? 💬👇

“Sunscreen blocks vitamin D!” — sounds logical, but it’s NOT true. ❌

Let’s bust this myth once and for all! 🧴✨

Even with sunscreen, your body still makes enough vitamin D — because:
✅ Most people don’t apply enough SPF everywhere
✅ A small amount of UV is enough for your body to produce vitamin D
✅ Studies show regular SPF use doesn’t lead to deficiency

So don’t skip your sunscreen — it protects you from premature ageing & skin cancer, without robbing your glow or health. 😎🛡️

🎥 Share this with a friend who still thinks SPF = no vitamin D!

Don’t fall for fear-mongering!
Chemical sunscreens are safe, effective, and essential — backed by real science, not viral myths.

Some ingredients get absorbed, but studies show no harm or cancer risk in humans.

The real danger? Skipping sunscreen altogether and letting UV damage your skin.
Choose your sunscreen wisely — but choose sunscreen always.
